node.text:
/ IT’S MY BIRTHDAY 🎉🎂
• where do i begin? today i turn 29 years old- a lot of you probably didn’t know that and some of you did!
i’d love to tell you all a bit on how i got started into this whole photography thing...

when i was in 10th grade in high school my parents bought me my first camera for having good grades and it was from that point on where i started to take photos of my friends- i started to share my work online not really expecting anything out of it.

as the years went by of sharing my work i started to meet so awesome people and started to get amazing opportunities (which i’m very thankful for to this day).

to be completely honest with you all- my goal was never to become a photographer that a lot of people knew about- i never started photography to get followers or any of that- i was just simply in love with the art of it. 

throughout the years i started meeting a lot of people in the social media space who i started collaborating with and giving them photos to share on their platforms- never did i think anyone would care to keep up with my work because of that.

the most important thing for me throughout all this was always to build a friendship with everyone. i’ve always felt that being friends with the people you work with is a lot better anyways and you also tend to really capture the best moments because of that.

to completely honest with you all- i look at myself at this point as the older brother to so many people around me and i always do my best to give them the best advice from everything i’ve learned in my years of being in this space. i’m constantly giving everyone advice and wishing the best for them.

i feel like i’ve done a pretty bad job at showing my personality online because i’ve always been so focused at sharing my work with you all- but i’m so ready to change that this year.

anyways- i wanted to thank you all so so much for being a follower and supporter of my work- it means the world to me.

if you made it this far reading this... comment: “love” 

❤️🥳🎂🎉
